column1: #Text=Polycrystalline Mn2MnWO6 was prepared from a stoichiometric mixture of MnO (99.99%, Alfa Aesar) and WO3 (99.8%, Alfa Aesar) at 1673 K under 8 GPa for 1 h in a Multi-Anvil Press as used in our previous work7,8,9, 53.
#Text=SPXD data were recorded on beam line X-16C (λ = 0.69991 Å) at the Brookhaven National Synchrotron Light Source.
#Text=Diffraction data analysis and Rietveld refinement were performed with the TOPAS software package54, 55.

#Text=NPD data were collected on 0.1063 g sample (placed inside a 3 mm diameter vanadium can with sample height around 4 mm) at the ISIS Neutron source (Rutherford Appleton Laboratory (UK)) on the WISH diffractometer located at the second target station56.
#Text=Data were collected at 290 K (~ 1 h) and then the sample was cooled to 5 K in an Oxford Instruments cryostat and a high quality data set was recorded (~ 3 h).
#Text=Shorter scans were then collected on warming (~ 35 minute scans in 5 K increments to 80 K, then at 90 and 100 K).
#Text=Rietveld refinements were carried out with Topas-Academic54, 55 (for 290 K data) and Jana200657, for 5 K and intermediate temperature nuclear and magnetic structures).
#Text=The magnetic symmetry analysis was carried out using ISODISTORT58.
#Text=Double-frame data sets were collected at 5 and 100 K to confirm the presence of a magnetic Bragg reflection at ~ 47 Å below T N.
#Text=The Mn-K and W-L3 XANES data were collected in both the transmission and fluorescence mode with simultaneous standards.
#Text=All of the spectra were fitted to linear pre- and post-edge backgrounds and normalized to unity absorption edge step across the edge4, 7, 8, 59, 60.
#Text=All of the XANES was performed on beam line X-19A at the Brookhaven National Synchrotron Light Source with a Si-111 double crystal monochromator.
